I am irresistibly drawn to recall an incident at the San Diego Zoo on a determinate date. I was viewing a display of tortoises when a gaggle of Bright Young Things (presumably SDZ volunteers) scampered past. One exclaimed, 'I didn't know we had turtles!'

The distinction between turtles and tortoises was explained, to no apparent purpose.







